<TITLE> Barisal Shibir top brass held </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Barisal, May 27 (bdnews24.com)  Police have arrested six activists of the Islami Chhatra Shibir's Barisal unit including its president and general secretary. They were arrested for staging a human chain on Thursday 'without prior permission'. Later they were produced before a court shown arrested under Section 54. The Islami Chhatra Shibir is the student front of the fundamentalist Jamaat-e-Islami, which is a major ally of the main opposition BNP. The detainees are, president Saiful Islam, general secretary Kazi Saiful Islam, district (west) president Azam Khan, district (east) president Nasir Uddin, activists Ruhul Amin and Mizanur Rahman. Police said the event, protesting drug abuse, smoking, eve-teasing and vulgarity, took place at Ashwini Kumar Hall premises in the city at around 10am. Sub inspector of the Kotwali Police station Anwar Hossain told reporters: "Hearing of the demonstration, police went to the spot, charged batons and dispersed the activists." "The six were arrested from the spot," he added. bdnews24.co
